                            Severus wrote a letter to
                            Caesaria Hypatissa explaining
                            a woman should not take the eucharist following sex or during menstruation.
                            
                                
                            
                         <a href="/3197-1" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><hr/><p class="indent"><span class="spearLabel">event: </span>
                            Severus wrote a letter to 
                            Thomas discussing
                            purity and fasting.
                            
                                
                            
                        The identification of this Thomas is not clear. <a href="/3165-1" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><hr/><p class="indent"><span class="spearLabel">event: </span>
                            Severus sent a
                            letter to Cassian concerning the vexing question of the ordination
                            of Dorotheus
                            who had been castrated by a physician and not of his own will.  <a href="/3075-18" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><hr/><p class="indent"><span class="spearLabel">event: </span>
                            Caesaria Hypatissa wrote a letter to
                            Severus asking about
                            whether or not a woman should take the eucharist following sex or during menstruation.
                            
                                
                            
                         <a href="/3197-2" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><hr/><p class="indent"><span class="spearLabel">event: </span>For five
                                yearsthe
                                community attracted many into their company, some coming
                            as far as Ingilene. All were impressed by the religious devotion
                                of the
                                community; all who joined them turned from sin,
                            committing their lives to prayer, worship, singing, and monastic
                            devotion.  <a href="/827-3" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><hr/><p class="indent"><span class="spearLabel">event: </span>Abbi warns
                                John of
                                Ephesus about purity and chastity.  <a href="/806-8" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><hr/><div class="citation"><h3>How to cite:</h3><span class="element">
